# UI Interaction Consistency

- Follow established CRUD interaction pattern:
  - Add/edit through sheet forms
  - Row actions through context menu
  - Clear user feedback through toasts
- Keep action labels and behavior consistent across Clients, Projects, and Orders.
- Keep sheet footer behavior consistent:
  - submit
  - clear
  - cancel
- Preserve left alignment, bottom anchoring, and non-stretched action buttons in sheet forms.
- Reuse shared app-level components in `src/app/shared/components/` for repeated UI patterns.

## Combobox stability pattern (important)

- For searchable comboboxes, treat selected id (`selected...Id`) as source of truth.
- Treat query/display text controls (`...Query`) as UI text only; do not make them the only required validity gate.
- Do not re-resolve selected ids from query text during submit; submit should use selected id state.
- `searchChange` should update visible text and clear lookup errors, but should not aggressively clear valid selected ids due to transient combobox event ordering.
